glischsprachige Literatur wird berücksichtigt. Drei italienische Autoren von Autobiographien kommen ebenfalls zu Wort und nehmen zu ihrem Werk Stellung. Die theoretische Reflexion, die die Analyse einzelner Werke begleitet oder auch selbständig durchgeführt wird, betrifft einerseits das Verhältnis von Autobiographie und 'Autofiktion', und andererseits die grundsätzliche Frage, was es heißt, von 'jüdischen Autobiographien' zu reden.  aThe proceedings of the conference of the same name assemble papers concentrating largely on Franco-Jewish autobiography in the last few decades. Relevant literature in English and German is also discussed. In addition, three Italian authors of autobiographies comment on their own works. The theoretical reflection undertaken in the volume either accompanies the analysis of individual works or takes a broader view. It centres (a) on the relationship between autobiography and 'auto-fiction', and (b) on the fundamental issue of what we precisely mean when we speak of 'Jewish autobiographies'.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAutobiographyxJewish authorsvCongresses. 0aJewsvBiographyvCongresses. 4aAutobiographie. 4aJuden. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aChiantaretto, Jean-François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFubini, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHilfrich, Carola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLecarme, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLezzi, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela